  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>This robed man turns a golden-bespectacled gaze and winning smile on you. He seems a charming-enough sort, but it's clear he wants something from you and is perfectly willing to take it - politely and with absolute guile, of course.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>Omahdon brightens as he sees you. "Hello again, friend. Any news of Perseia? Have you seen her?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Ask Omahdon for further details about his lost love.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"As I said, she is hauntingly beautiful, with purple hair that floats around her head on winged combs. Her speech may seem confused, so pay no mind to what she says. It is only her madness talking. Once she is returned to me, I will be able to cure her."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I found this comb in Tranquility's hostel. It has purple hair caught in it. Is it Perseia's?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes! That is one of her combs! Incredible!"

He takes it from you with great care. "I knew that witch was lying to me! She told me that Perseia had never stayed with her. Please, go to Tranquility and ask her where Perseia went. Maybe she'll tell *you* the truth!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Perseia of your dreams doesn't exist. You're chasing a real woman who hates you. There is no happy ending here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>For a long moment, Omahdon looks like he's about to punch you, but then he turns away. "You're right. My Perseia was the one who slept. The one who woke was a stranger to me, and I have tortured both her and myself by trying to force her reality to match my fantasy. I have been a fool, and worse, a villain. She... she will not see me again."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>He snarls. "She only hates me because she doesn't know me. If she would just stand still, I would show her who I am, and then she couldn't help but love me! I *will* show her! Just as soon as I find her."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>For a long moment, Omahdon looks like he's about to punch you, but then he turns away. "You're right. My Perseia was the one who slept. The one who woke was a stranger to me, and I have tortured both her and myself by trying to force her reality to match my fantasy. I have been a fool, and worse, a villain. She... she will not see me again."

He bows to you. "Please take this. You have saved me from worse villainy. That is a gift beyond price."

{SCRIPT: Need some kind of reward.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Liar! You know nothing of our love! It was destined! And I will prove it to her! I will make her love me!"

{SCRIPT: No second try at DT?}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>(Truth) "Tranquility told me Perseia was indeed here, but she took a ship to the Valley of Dead Heroes."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>His brows furrow with concern. "She returns to the grave? That is worrying, but perhaps I will catch her in time. Thank you, friend - you have given me hope. Please take this as a reward. Now I must hurry. Farewell."

{LOOT}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tranquility told me that Perseia was here, but she took a ship to Sada Imidu."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>He smacks his fist into his palm. "Ha! I knew that witch was lying! I..."

He trails off and gives you a crafty look. "But maybe you are too. I think I'll talk to Tranquility and see if your stories match. Good day, friend."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>He shakes his head. "So Tranquility is trying to throw me off the scent by putting words in your mouth with her gentle wiles."

He pats your shoulder. "I don't blame you, friend. She's glamoured wiser folk than you. But I won't listen to you either, not while she's moving your lips. Now I know where Perseia *didn't* go."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>He smacks his fist into his palm. "Ha! I knew that witch was lying! Sada Imidu, is it? Then I'd better hurry - the next ship leaves on the turn of the wind."

He bows to you as he backs toward the docks. "Thank you, friend. You have done me a great service today."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>He glares at you. "So you've sided with Tranquility, and you're trying to throw me off the scent. Well, I won't be fooled, friend. I know a liar when I hear one."

He chuckles. "At least you've told me where Perseia *didn't* go."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>(Lie) "Go and talk to Tranquility. She regrets lying to you and wants to apologize. She'll tell you the truth this time."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tranquility told me that Perseia was here, but she took a ship to Haref."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>He smacks his fist into his palm. "Ha! I knew that witch was lying! I..."

He trails off and gives you a crafty look. "But maybe you are too. I think I'll talk to Tranquility and see if your stories match. Good day, friend."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
